<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC5FFE9A52E7E2E94D60FFC" box="[1063,1206,1396,1421]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" type="description">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE9A52E7E2E94D60FFC" blockId="12.[1063,1206,1396,1421]" box="[1063,1206,1396,1421]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">(63 SPECIES)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC5FFE8A2327EC7926F0B27" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1225" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE9A2327EC7943B0CF8" blockId="12.[827,1443,1436,1673]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A2327EC793D70FC3" box="[827,951,1437,1458]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small to massive adult-sized 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A4217EC695C20FC3" authorityName="D' ORBIGNY" authorityYear="1845" box="[1320,1442,1436,1458]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="order">Oegopsida</taxonomicName>
with modifications of the funnel–mantle locking apparatus; funnel–mantle locking apparatus reaching the anterior margin of the mantle; with two series of suckers in the arms; tentacle manus suckers usually in four series; mitochondrial gene 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A5CD7D6C949E0C3A" box="[1220,1278,1590,1611]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">trnM</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A4647D6C95C30C3A" box="[1389,1443,1590,1611]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">rrnL</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A2797D0F93C50C1B" box="[880,933,1621,1642]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">trnY</emphasis>
in the following sequence: 
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A5E67D0F94340CF8" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">−rrnL −trnM − trnY −trnW −trnG −trnE</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC5FFE8A2327DE8926F0B27" blockId="12.[827,1443,1714,1889]" lastBlockId="13.[145,760,197,342]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1225" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC5FFE9A2327DE893A10CB6" box="[827,961,1714,1735]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224">Synonyms:</emphasis>
The superfamilies 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A5B77DE895C10CB9" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[1214,1441,1714,1736]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Ommastrephoidea">Ommastrephoidea</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC5FFE9A2327D8B946A0C97" author="Steenstrup J" box="[827,1034,1744,1766]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" pagination="11 - 14" refId="ref17133" refString="Steenstrup J. 1857 b. Oplysning om en ny Art af Blaeksprutter, Dosidicus Eschrichtii. Oversigt over det Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskabs Forhandlinger 1857: 11 - 14." type="journal article" year="1857">Steenstrup, 1857b</bibRefCitation>
and Thysanoteuthoidea 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC5FFE9A42C7D8A93130D74" author="Keferstein W" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" pagination="1307 - 1464" refId="ref15533" refString="Keferstein W. 1866. Kopffusser: Cephalopoda Cuvier. In: Bronn HG, ed. Die Klassen und Ordnungen des Thierreiches: Weichthiere (Malacozoa). Leipzig: C. F. Winter, 1307 - 1464." type="book chapter" year="1866">Keferstein, 1866</bibRefCitation>
were described in a different sense than in the present work: the superfamily 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A5C97C5495C10D55" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[1216,1441,1806,1828]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Ommastrephoidea">Ommastrephoidea</taxonomicName>
included 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A2A77C7694E60D33" authorityName="Pfeffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[942,1158,1836,1858]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Brachioteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Brachioteuthidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A59F7C76950A0D33" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[1174,1386,1836,1858]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ommastrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Ommastrephidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC5FFE9A2327C11946A0D10" authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1866" box="[827,1034,1867,1889]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Thysanoteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Thysanoteuthidae</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC5FFE9A5967C16954E0D10" author="Berry SS" box="[1183,1326,1867,1889]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1224" pagination="141 - 169" refId="ref14237" refString="Berry SS. 1920. Light production in cephalopods, I. An introductory survey. Biological Bulletin 38: 141 - 169." type="journal article" year="1920">Berry (1920)</bibRefCitation>
. However, owing to our criteria the families 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A3237B9F92980AAA" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[554,760,197,219]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ommastrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Ommastrephidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A1C27BBE91D30A8B" authorityName="Keferstein" authorityYear="1866" box="[203,435,228,250]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Thysanoteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Thysanoteuthidae</taxonomicName>
are included within the superfamily 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A02D7A5891A20B69" authorityName="PROSCH" authorityYear="1847" box="[292,450,258,280]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cranchioidea">Cranchioidea</taxonomicName>
. We therefore consider the names 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A1EC7A7B91DC0B46" authorityName="Steenstrup" authorityYear="1857" box="[229,444,289,311]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1224" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Ommastrephoidea">Ommastrephoidea</taxonomicName>
and Thysanoteuthoidea as junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A0797A1A926B0B27" authorityName="PROSCH" authorityYear="1847" box="[368,523,320,342]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cranchioidea">Cranchioidea</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
